Mixins — composition via inheritance, done right.

A mixin is a class designed to be inherited from in combination with others, providing a focused set of methods. Mixins usually do not have dunder-init and do not make sense on their own.

The convention. Mixin class names end in mixin, or with an able suffix like comparable, iterable. The pattern shows up across the standard library and django.

In code, picture serializable-mixin with a to-dict method that returns the instance's dunder-dict filtered to public keys. Printable-mixin with a show method that calls to-dict and prints each entry. Class user of serializable-mixin and printable-mixin, with dunder-init taking name and email. Construct u, call u dot to-dict and u dot show — both methods compose cleanly.
